{"id":"math140-critical_pt120-ap003","cid":"MATH 140","topic":"Applications of Derivatives","subtopic":"Profit maximization","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A company's weekly profit (in thousands) is P(x) = {a}x^2 + {b}x + {c}, where x is price in dollars. Find the optimal price and maximum weekly profit.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":-1},"b":{"type":"int","min":12,"max":40},"c":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":60}},"answer_expr":"critical_pt120","steps":["Set P'(x) = {two_a}x + {b} = 0.","Optimal price: x = {x_star} dollars.","Maximum profit: P({x_star}) = {fx_star} thousand dollars."],"tags":["business-calculus","pricing","optimization","profit"]}
